==English==

===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''[[doctrina]]'', diminutive from ''[[doctus]]'', '''[[taught]]''', perfect passive participle of ''[[docere]]'', '''teach'''

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[belief]], especially about [[philosophical]] or [[theological]] matters.
# The [[teaching]]s of a [[religion]], or a religious [[leader]], [[organization]], [[group]] or [[text]]: e.g., "The incarnation is a basic doctrine of classical Christianity," "The four noble truths summarise the main doctrines of Buddhism."

